Laser welding is a process used to join together metals or thermoplastics using a laser beam to form a weld. The laser beam is absorbed only at the surface of the material and does not penetrate it. 🔥👨‍🏭⁣
⁣
Conduction limited welds often then exhibit a high width to depth ratio. The process is frequently used in high volume applications using automation, as in the automotive industry.⁣
📷: @peslaser⁣
